Art performance given by unionists
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- An art performance was given by unionists in Pyongyang yesterday on the occasion of the 4th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as General Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, the 56th anniversary of the WPK and the 75th anniversary of the Down-With-Imperialism Union.
 Present there was Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the c.c., the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, in his speech said that the proud path covered by the WPK adorning the arduous years of the revolution with victories and glory is associated with the immortal exploits of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stage was a multifarious program. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers sang of their biggest fortune and unbounded pride of being members of Kim Il Sung's nation and their firm determination to remain loyal to Kim Jong Il through various numbers including poem, chorus, mixed chorus.

Struggle for independence called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- The strength of the independent popular masses standing for justice is inexhaustible and no force can defeat them, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The trend of the situation in the new century calls on the progressives to vigorously struggle for peace, stability, prosperity and progress under the banner of the anti-imperialist struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Inexhaustible are the spiritual power and fighting spirit of the people, the driving force of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The source of strength of justice lies in the unity among people and the unity serves as a fundamental guarantee for achieving the popular masses' cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If broad segments of people around the world struggle in firm unity under the banner of independence, the banner of defending justice, they can foil any moves for aggression and strategy of strength of the imperialists, safeguard world peace and security and promote the global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an issue of special importance to increase national defense capability in building up the strength of the popular masses standing for justice. 
 One should not be afraid of imperialist aggressors but maintain the principle of national independence and not allow any slightest concession to them and retreat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hard line of the imperialists should be countered with a super hard line. This is a legitimate right of a country and nation advocating independence and a mode of independent counter-action to emerge victorious in the confrontation with imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world progressives will strengthen the force of justice and wage a strenuous anti-imperialist struggle under the banner of independence to powerfully advance the human cause of independence, the cause of peace, and build a new, free and peaceful world without fail.

New brewery near completion
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- The Taedonggang brewery under construction in the eastern part of Pyongyang is close to completion.
 94 percent of the construction of its buildings and 80 percent of the assembling of its equipment have been carried out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The construction of power line, drainage works, railway siding and unloading site is also near completion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the production processes of the brewery will be computerized and automated.
 The inside and outside of the brewery will fully meet the needs of culture and sanitation as a modern brewery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will have a large production capacity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The beer brewed there is expected to be very popular for its unique color and peculiar taste. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its main products will be bottled and barrelled beer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over 200 beer counters will be set up in various parts of Pyongyang.

Kim Jong Il sends greetings to Putin
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, Chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, on October 4 sent a message of greetings to Russian President Putin on his 49th birthday.
 Extending warm congratulations to Putin on his birthday, Kim Jong Il said that Russia is actively pushing forward the work to increase the country's defense capability and achieve the political stability and economic progress under his leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-Russia friendly relations with a long history and tradition were given a new definition and an opportunity to develop more viably by our recent meeting, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed conviction that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would grow in scope and strength on the basis of the results of the Moscow meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He sincerely wished him success in his work to build powerful Russia and good health and happiness.

IAEA's double standards rejected
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- The United States openly conducted another sub-critical nuclear test in an underground nuclear test site in Nevada state recently in utter disregard of the "comprehensive nuclear test ban treaty".
 In this regard Minju Joson today says in a signed commentary: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is the international atomic energy agency's double standards in dealing with the nuclear issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is beyond doubt that the IAEA is applying double standards in handling this issue. it persistently urges the country which is not to blame for any nuclear issue to accept verification and inspection, while keeping mum about the country which unceasingly conducts nuclear tests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is evidenced by the fact that the IAEA once again urged the DPRK to accept verification and inspection of its past nuclear activities under the pretext of coping with attacks on the united states. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not the DPRK but the U.S. that should accept the IAEA's verification and inspection. This is the unanimous and unbiased comment of the world public. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the IAEA decided to verify and inspects the nuclear facilities of the DPRK, not the U.S. This eloquently proves that the IAEA is applying double standards, dancing to the tune of others after departing from the principle of justice and impartiality in its activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a matter of fact, some dishonest elements of the IAEA are acting upon the script written by the united states, pursuant to its policy, in a bid to make "nuclear threat" from the DPRK an established fact. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is needless to say that this unjust stand will only result in crippling the international community's confidence in the IAEA and inviting strong worldwide protest and denunciation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will certainly make the IAEA pay a high price for persistently urging the DPRK to accept verification and inspection while uttering not a word about the U.S. which continues conducting nuclear tests in wanton violation of international conventions.
